OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F359A1776258665
OL,3,CRobert Burns' family flute played in
OL,4,CNew York to help save poet's home
OL,6,FA 200-year-old flute closely linked to
OL,7,FScotland's national poet will be
OL,8,Fplayed in New York City for the first
OL,9,Fever time, as part of a campaign to
OL,10,Fsave the farm on which Rabbie Burns
OL,11,Fwrote Auld Lang Syne.
OL,13,FThe historic instrument will be played
OL,14,Fduring 'Tartan Week 2026', in order to
OL,15,Fraise funds to secure the future of
OL,16,FEllisland, the only home built by
OL,17,FBurns himself.
OL,19,FThe Robert Burns Ellisland Trust says
OL,20,F#12million is needed to restore the
OL,21,Fsite, which dates from 1788.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G1/6
