OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,360,350,120,260,000,100
PN,35903
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F359A1776258665
OL,3,CRobert Burns' family flute played in
OL,4,CNew York to help save poet's home
OL,6,FThe farmstead and its collections have
OL,7,Fsuffered from years of weathering and
OL,8,Fstructural decay, and the charity
OL,9,Fwhich looks after the site says it
OL,10,Fneeds "urgent support".
OL,12,FThe flute to be played had lain silent
OL,13,Ffor centuries before a recent
OL,14,Frestoration.
OL,16,FIt was once owned by Burns' son, James
OL,17,FGlencairn Burns, who performed his
OL,18,Ffather's songs.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G3/6
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
